{"id": 8489, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2022", "session": "22M", "subtopic": "11-1-uncertainties-and-errors-in-measurement-and-results", "title": "22M.1.SL.TZ2.29", "topic_id": "11", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>What is the uncertainty, in cm<sup>3</sup>, of this measurement?<br/><img height=\"157\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" width=\"147\"/><br/>A.  ±0.01</p>\n<p>B.  ±0.1</p>\n<p>C.  ±0.15</p>\n<p>D.  ±1</p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>C</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>This question generated a lot of debate among teachers and examiners. The answer B is the best answer but it is a rather low value. It was selected by 34% of the candidates. Many teachers argued that the correct answer should be 0.5 cm<sup>3</sup>.</p>\n</div>"}